    <statement><p>Simplify the following expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain on the simplified expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{-6t^{2}-t^{3}}{t^{2}+5t-6}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{t^{2}}{t-1}, t\ne -6</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common factors:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{-6t^{2}-t^{3}}{t^{2}+5t-6}} \amp = \frac{{-t^{3}-6t^{2}}}{{\left(t+6\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{-t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(t+6\right)}}{{\left(t+6\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{t^{2}}{t-1}, t\ne -6}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>t+6</m> was crossed out, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne -6</m>.</p>
</solution>
